author: COMSOL
description: This introductory model illustrates two different ways to couple an electrical circuit model to a finite element simulation. In this case, the finite element part represents a cylindrical resistor in the circuit. The FEM model will be coupled to the circuit by either using two External I-Terminal features or by using an External I vs. U feature. Differences between the two approaches will then be highlighted.
